The Cu-MOF nanostructures were prepared via a solvothermal method [30]. A mixture of H3BTC (2.14 mmol) and Cu(NO3)2
                        .3H2O (3.1 mmol) was dissolved in ethanol (48 mL) with vigorous stirring for 10 min. The reaction mixture was transferred into a stainless steel autoclave lined with Teflon, heated at 120 °C for 12 h, and cooled down to room temperature (Fig. 1
                        ). The fine blue powders were collected by centrifuging at 7000 rpm for 10 min, washed with absolute ethanol, and vacuum dried at 70 °C for 12 h. Comprehensive details regarding the characterization of prepared samples can be summarized in the Supporting Information.
